[section#cpp.stringize
    [:en] The [`#] operator
    [:zh_CN] [`#] 运算符
[:en] [%[`#] operator] [%stringize[%[`#] operator]]
[:zh_CN] [%[`#] 运算符] [%字符串化[%[`#] 运算符]]
]

[para]
[:en] Each [`#] preprocessing token in the replacement list for a function-like macro
shall be followed by a parameter as the next preprocessing token in the replacement list.
[:zh_CN] 函数式宏的替换列表中的每个 [`#] 预处理记号后面应当跟着一个形参作为
替换列表中的下一个预处理记号。

[para]
[:en] A [+character string literal] is a [~string-literal] with no prefix.
[:zh_CN] [+字符字符串字面量]是没有前缀的[~字符串字面量]。

[:en] If, in the replacement list, a parameter is immediately preceded by a [`#]
preprocessing token, both are replaced by a single character string literal
preprocessing token that contains the spelling of the preprocessing token
sequence for the corresponding argument (excluding placemarker tokens).
[:zh_CN] 若在替换列表中，某形参前紧接一个 [`#] 预处理记号，则它们被替换为一个
字符串字面量预处理记号，其中包含对应实参的预处理记号序列（排除位置标记记号）的拼写。

[:en] Let the [+stringizing argument] be the preprocessing token sequence for the
corresponding argument with placemarker tokens removed.
[:zh_CN] 令[+字符串化实参]为对应实参的移除了位置标记记号后的预处理记号序列。

[:en] Each occurrence of whitespace between the stringizing argument[=']s
preprocessing tokens becomes a single space character in the character string literal.
[:zh_CN] 该字符串化实参的预处理记号之间的每个空白均变为字符串字面量中的一个空格字符。

[:en] Whitespace before the first preprocessing token and after the last
preprocessing token comprising the stringizing argument is deleted.
[:zh_CN] 处于构成该字符串化实参的第一个预处理记号之前和最后一个预处理记号之后的空白均被删除。

[:en] Otherwise, the original spelling of each preprocessing token in the stringizing
argument is retained in the character string literal, except for special
handling for producing the spelling of [~header-name]s, [~character-literal]s,
and [~string-literal]s (including the delimiting [=unicode(0022,quotation mark)] ([`""]))
contained within the preprocessing token: a [=unicode(005c,reverse solidus)]
character ([`\]) is inserted before each [=unicode(0022,quotation mark)] and
[=unicode(005c,reverse solidus)] character of a [~header-name], [~character-literal],
or [~string-literal], and each new-line character is replaced by the two-character sequence [`\n].
[:zh_CN] 除此之外，字符串化实参中的每个预处理记号的原始拼写方式均保留于字符串字面量中，
但为产生预处理记号中所包含的[~头文件名]、[~字符字面量]和[~字符串字面量]（包括
用作分隔的 [=unicode(005c,reverse solidus)] 字符）的拼写进行特殊处理：在[~头文件名]、
[~字符字面量]或[~字符串字面量]的每个 [=unicode(0022,quotation mark)] 和
[=unicode(005c,reverse solidus)] 字符之前插入一个 [=unicode(005c,reverse solidus)] 字符（[`\]）。

[:en] If the replacement that results is not a valid character string literal,
the program is ill-formed.
[:zh_CN] 若所产生的替换并不是有效的字符串字面量，则程序非良构。

[:en] The character string literal corresponding to an empty stringizing argument is [`""].
[:zh_CN] 对应于空字符串化实参的字符串字面量为 [`""]。

[:en] The order of evaluation of [`#] and [`##] operators is unspecified.
[:zh_CN] 未指明 [`#] 和 [`##] 运算符的求值顺序。
